    "originalText": "# Ricotta Gnocchi\n\nLight, pillowy homemade gnocchi made with ricotta cheese instead of potato. Serves 4.\n\n## Ingredients\n\n### Dough\n- 1 lb (454 g) full fat ricotta\n- 1.5 cups (190 g) all-purpose flour\n- 1/3 cup (33 g) grated parmesan cheese\n- 1 large egg\n\n## Equipment\n- Fine mesh sieve\n- Mixing bowl\n- Large pot\n- Cutting board and knife\n- Fork\n\n## Instructions\n\n1. Drain ricotta in a fine mesh sieve set over a bowl in the fridge for at least 1 hour.\n2. Add grated parmesan cheese and egg to the drained ricotta. Stir with a fork until blended.\n3. Add 1 cup of the flour and mix until just blended.\n4. Dump dough onto a floured surface and gently work into a soft ball, adding flour as needed.\n5. Break off baseball-sized pieces and roll into tubes about 1/2 to 1 inch thick.\n6. Cut tubes into 1 inch pieces and toss with flour to prevent sticking.\n7. Bring a large pot of salted water to a rolling boil.\n8. Drop gnocchi into the boiling water and remove them when they float to the surface (less than 5 minutes).\n9. Drain and toss with your desired sauce.\n\n## Notes\n\nDo not overwork the dough or the gnocchi will be tough. The ricotta must be well-drained for the right texture.",
